      "content": "If you want to lean into the earthy green, you have a few directions to go, depending on how much grounding you want. A slightly more saturated version will add a bit more presence, while a darker one will feel more weighty and established.\n\nHere are a few variations of earthy greens for your accent:\n\n*   **Slightly More Saturated Sage:** `#7A8E7A` (This is a bit brighter than the previous one, offering a touch more life while still remaining very muted.)\n*   **Deep Forest Green (Muted):** `#556B2F` (This is darker and richer, suggesting deep roots and unwavering stability. Use this sparingly, like for important headings.)\n*   **Warm Moss Green:** `#8F9779` (This sits nicely between the grey and the blue tones, offering a very organic, grounded feel.)\n\nConsider which shade best reflects the specific type of law your firm practices. If you deal with real estate, the deep forest green might be perfect. If you prefer a softer, more organic feel, the moss green is your friend.",
